<font color="#FF0000">RUSSIAN'S INVOLVEMENT IN IRAQ</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 12 12:20:27 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
The Washington Post REPORTED TODAY,that U.N. weapons inspectors have uncovered evidence that in 1995 Russia had agreed to sell Iraq sophisticated equipment that could be used to develop biological weapons. <br><br>
This disclosure, says the WP, puts a new spin on Russia's recent diplomatic efforts to modify the inspection procedures applying to Iraq: perhaps they are designed, not to head off a war, but to keep such mass destruction fingerprints from being lifted. <br><br>
Cook Barela
